The mall's security manager said the extra security was brought in to ensure order on Black Friday at the mall s shops."We have additional security officers and about 100 SAPS officers because we are tired of crime at Mall of Africa and we want to combat it for good " Braam Banard said."So far luckily we have had zero reports of crime on our premises. It's going well " he said.The mall trading as the biggest mall in Africa reported incidents of car theft when it opened its doors for the first time in April 2016 an event that saw huge traffic jams on the N1 freeway and most roads leading to Midrand.